 long\nintegration times will result in the deepest, largest, high-quality\nspectroscopic dataset of galaxies from z=1 to 12, spanning the history of the\nUniverse, from 400 million to 6 billion years after the big bang, i.e. covering\nthe most active half of cosmic history.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Jun 2013 20:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-06-28"}
