an-field theory but also\ndynamical-impurity and variational-cluster approximations that are specified by\nreference systems with a finite number of degrees of freedom. In this way,\nnon-perturbative and consistent approximations can be set up, the numerical\nevaluation of which is accessible to an exact-diagonalization approach.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Jun 2013 20:00:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 1 Jul 2013 16:50:12 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 18 Oct 2013 15:40:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-10-21"}
