commensurability of the Co-doped\ncompounds yields a larger ratio between the competing next-nearest neighbour\nand nearest neighbour interaction, which is $J_2/J_1$=0.43 (0.47) for a doping\nlevel of 7% (10%) Co compared to 0.39 in the parent compound.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Jun 2013 13:11:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 30 Jun 2013 18:49:23 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 16 Oct 2013 15:01:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-11-26"}
